  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of Water Sources in East Hararghe Zone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought affected/vulnerable households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of water supply systems. 

Organization of refresher trainings on improved hygiene and sanitation practices at different intervals.

Construction of 2,256 household latrines.

Training on construction and use of eco-toilets to 2,256 households.

Establishment and training of 28 WASH committees on water source Management Operation and Maintenance (O&amp;amp;M) and financial management.
 
Recruitment and training of 56 water caretakers. 

Provision of refresher trainings for existing water caretakers in water source infrastructure operations, maintenance and repair.
                                                 
Provision of maintenance tools and basic repair equipment to water caretakers for each rehabilitated water source.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is to assister disaster-affected populations improve their resiliency to drought, with 3,594 critically drought-affected households in Babile, Kersa and Meta Woredas have increased sustainable access to safe water.</narrative>
  </description>
